    <title>如何理解最小二乘法？</title>
    <url>/2020/12/28/2020-12-28-%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E7%90%86%E8%A7%A3%E6%9C%80%E5%B0%8F%E4%BA%8C%E4%B9%98%E6%B3%95/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>无论是传统的统计学，还是时下火热的机器学习，线性回归都是最基础但又十分重要的模型之一。线性回归使用了最小二乘法来估计模型参数，如何理解最小二乘法将成为掌握线性回归的关键。最小二乘法可以从定义、线性代数、概率论三个角度来理解，本文对此进行简单的整理。这样的整理不仅有助于我们学习线性回归，也有助于我们理解ridge回归、lasso回归等很多模型。接下来，我们就开始吧。</p>
<h1 id="从定义看最小二乘法"><a href="#从定义看最小二乘法" class="headerlink" title="从定义看最小二乘法"></a>从定义看最小二乘法</h1><p>简单线性回归模型通常设定为：<br>$$<br>y_i = ax_i+b+e_i<br>$$<br>我们的目的是求解a和b，但是我们希望求解出来的a和b能使得总的误差尽可能的小。也就是说，我们需要定义一个目标函数测量总误差，目标函数达到最小时的a和b，就是我们想要的a和b。</p>
<p>单条观测数据的误差可以直接定义为$y_i-ax_i-b$，那么总的误差也就是目标函数可以定义为$\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_i-ax_i-b)$，这样定义的误差有正有负，导致结果恒等于0，我们可以考虑将目标函数定义为$\sum_{i=1}^{n}|y_i-ax_i-b|$。这样的定义貌似解决了问题，但$|x|$不是一个处处可导的函数，这导致求解过程却遇到了麻烦，最终统计学家将线性回归的目标函数定义如下：<br>$$<br>J(a,b)=\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_i-ax_i-b)^2<br>$$<br>这种定义目标函数的方法就是最小二乘法，最小就是求解最小值，二乘就是乘两次，同一个数据乘两次就是平方，这就是最小二乘法的基本含义，正因为如此，最小二乘法又被称为最小平方法。有了目标函数，接下来就是求解参数a和b，这是一个最优化问题，需要一些微积分的知识：<br>$$<br>arg\min_{a,b}\sum_{i=1}^{n}(y_i-ax_i-b)^2<br>$$<br>微积分中，函数的极值往往在导数为0处出现。参数b看上去求解更加简单，可以先进行求解，令：<br>$$<br>\frac{\partial J(a,b)}{\partial b}=0\<br>$$<br>这是一个复合函数求导问题，根据链式求导法则，可知：<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n 2(y_i-ax_i-b)(-1)=0\<br>$$<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n (y_i-ax_i-b)=0\<br>$$</p>
<p>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^ny_i-a\sum_{i=1}^nx_i=\sum_{i=1}^nb<br>$$</p>
<p>由此可得：<br>$$<br>n*b=\sum_{i=1}^ny_i-a\sum_{i=1}^nx_i\<br>$$<br>$$<br>b=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^ny_i-a\sum_{i=1}^nx_i}{n}<br>$$</p>
<p>对上面公式再进行进一步的简化，我们就得到了参数b的解：<br>$$<br>b=\bar{y}-a\bar{x}<br>$$<br>然后我们求解参数a，令：<br>$$<br>\frac{\partial{J(a,b)}}{\partial{a}}=0\<br>$$<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(2(y_i-ax_i-b)(-x_i))=0\<br>$$<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-ax_i-b)x_i=0\<br>$$</p>
<p>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-ax_i^2-bx_i)=0<br>$$</p>
<p>将b带入上式中：<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-ax_i^2-\bar{y}x_i+a\bar{x}x_i)=0\<br>$$<br>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-\bar{y}x_i)-a\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i^2-\bar{x}x_i)=0\<br>$$</p>
<p>$$<br>\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-\bar{y}x_i)=a\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i^2-\bar{x}x_i)\<br>$$</p>
<p>$$<br>a = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-\bar{y}x_i)}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i^2-\bar{x}x_i)}<br>$$</p>
<p>利用公式$\sum{x_i}=\sum{\bar{x}}$，可以得到：<br>$$<br>a = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(y_ix_i-\bar{y}x_i+\bar{x}\bar{y}-\bar{x}{y_i})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i^2-\bar{x}x_i+\bar{x}^2-\bar{x}x_i)}\<br>$$<br>$$<br>a=\frac{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-\bar{y})}{\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2}<br>$$</p>
<p>这就得到了简单线性回归模型的参数a和b。</p>
<h1 id="从线性代数看最小二乘法"><a href="#从线性代数看最小二乘法" class="headerlink" title="从线性代数看最小二乘法"></a>从线性代数看最小二乘法</h1><p>以上我们从定义层面看了一下最小二乘法，并使用微积分工具求解了回归模型的参数，接下来我们从线性代数的角度来看一下线性回归问题。我们重写一下线性回归模型：<br>$$<br>y_i = {a}x_i+{b}+e_i<br>$$<br>用线性代数来表达上面的模型为：<br>$$<br>Y=X{β}+e<br>$$<br>其中，$Y、e$都是$n<em>1$的列向量，$β$是$2</em>1$的列向量，代表参数a和b，$X$为$n*2$的矩阵，矩阵的第一列为常数1，用来估计参数b，第二列为数据列，用来估计参数a。</p>
<p>从线性代数的角度来说，$Y、e$以及$X$的每一列都是n维空间中从原点发出的直线，而$Xβ$则是矩阵$X$列空间中的一条直线。最小化$e=Y-Xβ$，其实就是要在$X$的列空间中寻找一条直线使得$Xβ$到$Y$的距离最小。从几何上看，当$Xβ$是$Y$在列空间中的投影时，也即$e$与列空间正交时，这个距离是最小的，如下图所示：</p>
<p><img src="C:\Users\yujie\Desktop\微信图片_20210113214544.png" alt="微信图片_20210113214544"></p>
<p>$e$与列空间正交，意味着$e$与$X$中的每个列都正交，因此可得：<br>$$<br>X^T(Y-X{β})=0<br>$$<br>从而得到：<br>$$<br>{β}=(X^TX)^{-1}X^TY<br>$$<br>这就是线性回归的线性代数解。从线性代数的角度来理解最小二乘法，其实更加简单和直观。</p>
<h1 id="从概率论来看最小二乘法"><a href="#从概率论来看最小二乘法" class="headerlink" title="从概率论来看最小二乘法"></a>从概率论来看最小二乘法</h1><p>现在我们将考虑问题的方式切换到概率的角度。概率论中，我们常常将事件的发生假定服从一个概率分布，然后我们可以借助极大似然法来估计这一概率分布的参数。线性回归问题中，我们采集的每一条数据都可以视为一个随机事件，可以假定每条数据都服从一个相同的分布，我们最先想到的应该是正态分布，毕竟正态分布非常常见，即$P(Y_i)$：<br>$$<br>P(Y_i)\sim N(μ,σ^2)<br>$$<br>很显然这里的$μ$应该就是y的估计值$ax_i+b$，我们写出完整的概率密度函数<br>$$<br>P(Y_i)=\frac{1}{\sqrt{2π}σ}exp(-\frac{(y_i-ax_i-b)^2}{2σ^2})<br>$$<br>根据极大似然估计的思想，在满足独立同分布的假定下，我们写出似然函数：<br>$$<br>L=\prod_i^n\frac{1}{\sqrt{2π}σ}exp(-\frac{(y_i-ax_i-b)^2}{2σ^2})<br>$$<br>稍作变换可得：<br>$$<br>L=(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2π}σ})^nexp\sum_i^n(-\frac{(y_i-ax_i-b)^2}{2σ^2})\<br>L=(\frac{1}{\sqrt{2π}σ})^nexp(-\frac{1})\sum_i^n{(y_i-ax_i-b)^2}<br>$$<br>现在我们的目标是使$L$达到最大来估计参数a和b，仔细观察我们就会发现，我们的似然函数是一个单调函数，且指数为负数，还是一个减函数，最大化$L$其实等价于最小化如下函数：<br>$$<br>\sum_i^n{(y_i-ax_i-b)^2}<br>$$<br>可以看到，这个函数和根据最小二乘定义构造的目标函数完全相同。因此，我们很清楚了：<strong>最小二乘估计等价于数据服从正态分布时的极大似然估计</strong>。</p>
<h1 id="总结"><a href="#总结" class="headerlink" title="总结"></a>总结</h1><p>以上就是线性回归的不同理解，我们总结一下。从定义上来看，最小二乘法定义为最小化离差平方和；从线性代数得角度来看，最小二乘法本质上是在求解因变量在设计矩阵列空间的投影，从概率论的角度来看，最小二乘估计等价于数据付出从正态分布时的极大似然估计。</p>
<p>最后我们根据求解的公式来设计一个我们自己的简单线性回归类，初步考虑，线性回归类应该至少包括三个方法：</p>
<ul>
<li>构造方法</li>
<li>模型拟合方法</li>
<li>模型预测方法</li>
</ul>
<figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> numpy <span class="keyword">as</span> np</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">SimpleLinearRegression</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__init__</span>(<span class="params">self, x, y</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">assert</span> <span class="built_in">len</span>(x) == <span class="built_in">len</span>(y), \</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="string">&#x27;Simple linear regression reqires the length of x is equal to the length of y&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line">        self.x = x</span><br><span class="line">        self.y = y</span><br><span class="line">        self._a = <span class="literal">None</span></span><br><span class="line">        self._b = <span class="literal">None</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__str__</span>(<span class="params">self</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">&#x27;&#123;&#125;,you can fit a simple linear regression by calling the method of fit and make a prediction by calling the method of predict&#x27;</span>.<span class="built_in">format</span>(self.__class__)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__repr__</span>(<span class="params">self</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="string">&#x27;Simple Linear Regression class at &#123;&#125;&#x27;</span>.<span class="built_in">format</span>(<span class="built_in">hex</span>(<span class="built_in">id</span>(self)))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">fit</span>(<span class="params">self</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="string">&quot;&quot;&quot;you can use this method to fit a simple linear regression&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class="line">        x_mean = np.mean(self.x)</span><br><span class="line">        y_mean = np.mean(self.y)</span><br><span class="line">        num = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">        den = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">for</span> x_i, y_i <span class="keyword">in</span> <span class="built_in">zip</span>(x, y):</span><br><span class="line">            num += (x_i - x_mean) * (y_i - y_mean)</span><br><span class="line">            den += (x_i - x_mean) ** <span class="number">2</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">        self._a = num / den</span><br><span class="line">        self._b = y_mean - self._a * x_mean</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> self</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">fit2</span>(<span class="params">self</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="string">&quot;&quot;&quot;you can use this method to fit a simple linear regression&quot;&quot;&quot;</span></span><br><span class="line">        x_mean = np.mean(self.x)</span><br><span class="line">        y_mean = np.mean(self.y)</span><br><span class="line">        num = np.dot(x-x_mean,y-y_mean)</span><br><span class="line">        den = np.dot(x-x_mean,x-x_mean)</span><br><span class="line">        self._a = num/den</span><br><span class="line">        self._b = y_mean - self._a * x_mean</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> self</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">predict</span>(<span class="params">self, x_predict</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">assert</span> self._a <span class="keyword">is</span> <span class="keyword">not</span> <span class="literal">None</span> <span class="keyword">and</span> self._b <span class="keyword">is</span> <span class="keyword">not</span> <span class="literal">None</span>, \</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="string">&#x27;Please fit the model before calling the predict function&#x27;</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> <span class="built_in">isinstance</span>(x_predict,<span class="built_in">int</span>):</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">return</span> self.__predict(x_predict)</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">else</span>:</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">return</span> np.array([self.__predict(i) <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> x_predict])</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__predict</span>(<span class="params">self, x_predict_i</span>):</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> self._a * x_predict_i + self._b</span><br><span class="line">    </span><br><span class="line">    </span><br><span class="line">&gt;[<span class="number">0.45293553</span> <span class="number">0.85601313</span> <span class="number">1.66216834</span>]</span><br><span class="line">&lt;class &#x27;__main__.SimpleLinearRegression&#x27;&gt;,you can fit a simple linear regression by calling the method of fit and make a prediction by calling the method of predict</span><br><span class="line"><span class="number">0.40307760585901276</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="number">0.049857919190661626</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="number">0.4529355250496744</span></span><br><span class="line">&lt;class &#x27;__main__.SimpleLinearRegression&#x27;&gt;,you can fit a simple linear regression by calling the method of fit and make a prediction by calling the method of predict</span><br><span class="line"><span class="number">0.40307760585901276</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="number">0.049857919190661626</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>这里设计了fit和fit2两个方法来拟合模型，前者使用循环来实现累加运算，后者使用numpy的向量化运算来求解模型参数，显然后者的性能更高一些。</p>
]]></content>
